commit_message:
Convert bool/int values into string for string properties

Instead of rising an exception, boolean and integer values are
converted into string if string is expected.

Change-Id: I1e0014576c4df447bfa1595c530f1e24f411195d
Closes-Bug: #1367375

Ignore all dotfiles in the base dir of the tree except for

This should solve the "ignore my IDE's files" problem in a
general way.

Change-Id: I689220b303d24c65c5fe9523eadc8ad48a93737f

commit_message:
gitignore /.*

Ignore all dotfiles in the base dir of the tree except for
.gitignore.

This should solve the "ignore my IDE's files" problem in a
general way.

Change-Id: I689220b303d24c65c5fe9523eadc8ad48a93737f

commit_message:
Remove TESTR_FULL option for running tempest

The TESTR_FULL option was added back when tempest was running by
default with nosestests serially to test using testr in parallel.
However, this migration happened >1yr ago and the testr-full job is
just a duplicate of the regular full now. This commit removes the
option of running with TESTR_FULL to prevent confusion.

Change-Id: I57d1b249ced3d68143da7f514136d3b2e5deffd2

commit_message:
Fwaas API Test Enhancement

Add Test to insert and remove firewall rule to firewall policy

-Create a firewall rule
-Create a firewall policy
-Insert a firewall rule to policy
-Validate the insertion of rule to policy
-Remove the firewall rule from policy
-Validate the removal of firewall rule from policy

Change-Id: I3c9711294e1e6323bdad4ff783de1ed19e133c1b

commit_message:
Stop n-cpu by correct process name /w fake

When VIRT_DRIVER=fake, n-cpu processes are numbered (ie, n-cpu-1) in
start_nova. However, this scheme is not taken into account when
stopping nova, resulting in leftover n-cpu processes that fail
grenade's stop-base if USE_SCREEN=False. This special cases for the
fake driver in stop_nova_compute and ensures n-cpu(s) is shutdown
correctly.

Change-Id: Icebece9eadc4e10bb12fe4fdd2fa37d5f3983f66
Close-bug: #1378112

commit_message:
Retry getting the list of service plugins

On systems that start both neutron-server and neutron-l3-agent together,
there is a chance that the first call to neutron will timeout. Retry upto
4 more times to avoid the l3 agent exiting on startup.

This should make the l3 agent a little more robust on startup but still
not ideal, ideally it wouldn't exit and retry periodically.

Change-Id: I2171a164f3f77bccd89895d73c1c8d67f7190488
Closes-Bug: #1353953
Closes-Bug: #1368152
Closes-Bug: #1368795
(cherry picked from commit e7f0b56d74fbfbb08a3b7a0d2da4cefb6fe2aa67)

commit_message:
Better check for pypi mirror host connectivity

Now that we have switched to region specific mirrors, we
should look at the pip.conf for the host url/ip and try
the ping/http check on that specific mirror

Change-Id: I28e5988bc7b957f575323778589a974cb51dc7fd

commit_message:
Correct swift service name in docs

The docs incorrectly show an example of:

  enable_service swift

This does not work, it must be enabled on a per swift service
basis, like:

  enable_service s-proxy s-object s-container s-account

Change-Id: Ib4ed8b43f777d308f5464d45dc87735e843c0daf

and in NoopFirewall driver class.

commit_message:
Removed python26 from StoryBoard build.

In an effort to move away from outdated and poorly ported
technologies, we are removing support for python 2.6.

Change-Id: Ifae93d3bd771a2ddd528329a59b30c370d1739f6

Skip IPv6 Tests in the OpenContrail plugin

Similar to the way we are skipping tests in the OneConvergence plugin,
introduced by Kevin Benton in 9294de441e684a81f6e802ba0564083f1ad319d6.

Make code more python-like

Remove uneeded parens.
Use only one underscore.
Remove repetitive statements.

commit_message:
Support building wheels (PEP-427)

Universal is used to identify pure-Python module(by bdist_wheel). For
these, it is sufficient to build a wheel with _any_ Python ABI version
and publish that to PyPI (by whatever means).

Change-Id: I4315a0fed1c2f20c9997c58bdca40354e8093cb3

commit_message:
Add test jobs for devstack-precise-dib images

Next step in migrating to dib is moving to devstack-precise-dib images
in hpcloud. We have images and slaves built with dib for this label now
we need to run tests on those nodes. Add experimental jobs to
devstack-gate for nova network and neutron run against icehouse on these
new -dib images.

Change-Id: I3efb17d93173091827623c15704e5a79be8fca33

commit_message:
Improve query for alarmed metrics

Use joins to change three queries into one. Add a test that
showed a bug in the previous code

Changed to use a simpler way of creating the SubAlarm when
queried

Change-Id: I44ed4a6283b156d387564d1b802f2cd06f59bc8c

revisions:
[{'created': '2014-06-28 17:57:18.000000000', 'message': "Add profiling support to cinder

To be able to create profiling traces in Cinder, client should be
able to send special HTTP header that contains trace info.

This patch is as well important to be able to make cross project
traces. (Typical case nova calls cinder via python client, if
profiler is initialized in nova, cinder client will add extra
header, that will be parsed by special osprofiler middleware in cinder
api)

Don't worry no security issue here, trace information is signed by HMAC
key that is setted in api-paste.ini. So only person that knows HMAC key
is able to send proper header.

Change-Id: I53bb1b92e62841a02f941bdafaed7f8ed5db7ce1

commit_message:
Add profiling support to cinderclient

To be able to create profiling traces for Cinder, client should be
able to send special HTTP header that contains trace info.

This patch is as well important to be able to make cross project
traces. (Typical case nova calls cinder via python client, if
profiler is initialized in nova, cinder client will add extra
header, that will be parsed by special osprofiler middleware in cinder
api)

Don't worry no security issue here, trace information is signed by HMAC
key that is setted in api-paste.ini. So only person that knows HMAC key
is able to send proper header.

Main patch (in Cinder) is:
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/103415/

Change-Id: I53bb1b92e62841a02f941bdafaed7f8ed5db7ce1

commit_message:
Fix issues with object related commands

1) Can't create instance of swiftclient. Since we now create
an API instance, creating a swiftclient instance won't work.
Trying to do any object related command fails.

2) Listing objects in a container fails, we depend on the
data returned in a specific way, during the API transition
this must have slipped through.

Needs regression/funcitonal tests to mame sure this doesn't
happen again.

Change-Id: I69079a0dc9f32b84e6f9307729d3dbbba549ac5e

commit_message:
Fix broken cert revocation

Cert revocation was broken by
32b0adb591f80ad2c5c19519b4ffc2b55dbea672.  os.chdir() never returns
anything, so this method would always raise an exception.  The proper
way to handle an error from os.chdir() is to catch OSError.

There were existing tests for this code, but they conveniently mocked
os.chdir() to return values that are never actually returned.  The
tests were fixed to match the real behavior.

Change-Id: I7549bb60a7d43d53d6f81eecea31cbb9720cc8b6
Closes-bug: #1376368

commit_message:
Support Cinder API version 2

Add support for the second version of the Cinder API, which brings
useful improvements and will soon replace version one.

Add a new 'cinder_api_version' option in sahara.conf.

Implements: blueprint support-cinder-api-v2

commit_message:
Use OpenStack branding for trove client

Add oslosphinx to get OpenStack branding.
Remove html_static_path since it's unused and issues a warning.
Update copyright year.

Change-Id: I0bdcab8ebc5a201a3f91b4a6c4724536d1157901

commit_message:
Fix metadata overall limits bug

Currently metadata limits are checked on a per request basis. If
multiple requests are sent within the per request limits, it is
possible to exceed the overall limits.  This patch adds an overall
metadata check to ensure that multiple requests to add metadata to
an account/container will check overall limits before adding
the additional metadata.

This is a backport to the stable/icehouse branch for commit SHA
5b2c27a5874c2b5b0a333e4955b03544f6a8119f.

Closes-Bug: 1365350

Conflicts:
	swift/common/db.py
	swift/container/server.py

Change-Id: Id9fca209c9c1216f1949de7108bbe332808f1045

EqualLogic array CLI operation timeout causes the
SSH thread to be aborted. This would cause SSH
sessions to be orphaned and hit a max connection
limit on the array. This fix catches these aborts

commit_message:
Handle eqlx SSH connection close on abort.

EqualLogic array CLI operation timeout causes the
SSH thread to be aborted. This would cause SSH
sessions to be orphaned and hit a max connection
limit on the array. This fix catches these aborts
and makes sure the connection is closed.

Change-Id: I9392fd5dd79eb44f252bf50217f17cc473e6f2f0
Closes-Bug: 1374613
(cherry picked from commit 5cb23b67c53437fc51a6b37acac477fba4d6a7ab)

commit_message:
Clear hash ring cache in get_topic_for*

This causes the hash ring to be reset on each API request, avoiding
an issue where a new conductor never joins the ring until the API
service is restarted.

Closes-Bug: 1378570

Change-Id: Ic57370163f2f833efab662837036298f29f4ca90

commit_message:
Initial centos7 support for build-image.sh

Add some filtering to 55-cache-devsatck-repos to handle centos7, which
actually gets setup with a DISTRO_NAME of rhel7 in devstack

Update the readme file to highlight the options for building other
images.

"DISTRO=centos7 ./tools/build-image.sh" creates a workable centos7
qcow image with this change and a d-i-b that includes
Ie24033468b78587ea87188ee1b843b26895798ff

Change-Id: Ida38cba0a303ab77432d5d354f1952e00ebfa00e

commit_message:
Stop supplying DIB_RELEASE

dib already picks DIB_RELEASE out of the env, and us setting a default
subverts its ability to do the right thing in elements. Similarly,
the DIB_IMAGE_NAME is both not a dib env var and was not being used, nor
was DIB_IMAGE_FILENAME.

Change-Id: I0522bad3a4be6d81d225fec37a08c7c71a65fe4d

commit_message:
Support building wheels (PEP-427)

Universal is used to identify pure-Python module(by bdist_wheel). For
these, it is sufficient to build a wheel with _any_ Python ABI version
and publish that to PyPI (by whatever means).

Change-Id: I25af4512f3e7198d03828a87bdca719cb7105d7b

commit_message:
L3 Agent should generate ns_name in a single place

Currently the l3 agent has 2 places where it allows generating ns_name
of specific router_ids (ie. qrouter-<router_id>): in the RouterInfo's
constructor, and in _cleanup_namespaces. This patch proposes a
unification of this creation code with a property which lives in
RouterInfo's namespace. A simpler fix was also made for snat_ns_name.

This patch also offers a single way to initialize a new RouterInfo.

Related-bug: #1374946
Related-bug: #1374947
Change-Id: Ia028236b73a22ff534acee00b46c86b134dc987e

commit_message:
Support building wheels (PEP-427)

Universal is used to identify pure-Python module(by bdist_wheel). For
these, it is sufficient to build a wheel with _any_ Python ABI version
and publish that to PyPI (by whatever means).

Change-Id: I41969e5bcc5873f81ab306935327622cd770a629

commit_message:
DO NOT MERGE: log when bdm wrapper doesn't have connection_info

There is a race in nova.compute.manager.detach_volume where the bdm
retrieved from the database doesn't have connection_info set and we're
hitting a TypeError when trying to deserialize it.

My theory is that it's being set to None in the driver block_device
wrapper code so log exceptions when connection_info isn't set on
_transform and save.

Related-Bug: #1348204

Change-Id: I49b610f71f6915d5323bcdeeb081a055f20148b4

Keeping the order generates an error:
AttributeError: 'module' object has no attribute 'test_auth'

If you import manually the module in Python with your change, you will see that it's not an AttributeError, but an ImportError (stupid testtools). The problem is that "from six.moves import mock" cannot be used before openstack.common is defined. It doesn't look reliable.

I suggest to register mock move in tests/__init__.py instead of doing that in openstack/common/__init__.py.

By the way, the current move for mox doesn't work: try "python -m testtools.run tests.unit.test_loopingcall" and you get the same AttributeError (which is also an ImportError).

If we want to provide "mox" and "mock" moves as a feature of OpenStack common, we can define the move in openstack/common/__init__.py *and* tests/__init__.py. The six.add_movev() function uses setattr(), so it replaces the previous "move" with the same name. So it should work fine.

But other applications may hit the same bug (AttributeError/ImportError depending on the import order), so it's maybe safer to register the move in tests/__init__.py file of *each* project.

What do you think?'}, {'account_id': 6928, 'date': '2014-06-17 15:05:57.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 13: Code-Review-1

I think we should switch to using some simple synchronization with background processes (i.e. messages over pipe) instead. Although with this fix bug appears less often (~5 times less often), it's still there."}, {'account_id': 1297, 'date': '2014-09-05 19:21:55.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

I agree, it seems like a mulitprocessing event could be used (both processes share the event), when the first process has done what it needs to do it sets the event, the other process waits for that process to set the event before doing anything further. Would that work?'}, {'account_id': 6928, 'date': '2014-09-08 18:07:44.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: Workflow-1

Okay, I reproduced the failure locally, and based on the timing I think it has nothing to do with these sleep times.  I believe it's actually because I used the existence of the file to determine when the child had grabbed the lock, which is not necessarily true because it's a two-step process: create then lock.  So if the sequence goes:

child creates lock file
parent sees lock file
parent attempts to lock file
child attempts to lock file

We're dead because the parent is (correctly) able to lock the file, which would then block the child instead of the child blocking the parent as we want.  I think this can be pretty easily addressed, but I'll loop these tests locally to verify that it doesn't keep happening with that issue fixed.

Note that I still really don't want to add synchronization to these processes and threads for the reason noted in the code comment.  In fact, this race is exactly the sort of thing that might be missed if we had a separate method of synchronization.  In this case it was incorrect test code, but you could have a similar issue in the functional code where bad assumptions about atomicity were made.  If you force the lock operation to be atomic by synchronizing some other way then you could never catch such an error."}, {'account_id': 6928, 'date': '2014-09-10 23:19:57.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 2.'}, {'account_id': 6928, 'date': '2014-09-10 23:25:10.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

Okay, this one has run about 100000 iterations in my local environment without a failure, so I think the race causing the intermittent failures is solved.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2014-09-11 00:55:43.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Verified+1

revisions:
[{'created': '2014-09-04 17:59:28.000000000', 'message': "Sleep longer in external tests

I believe the intermittent failure in the linked bug is related to
not sleeping the test processes or threads long enough to ensure
that the other process/thread has a chance to execute.  While one
of the timeouts was set to 5 seconds, which was fine, the other was
.5, which is probably not an unreasonable length of time for a job
to be CPU starved in a heavily loaded system.

This changes the timeouts to be 60 and 5 seconds respectively.  The
60 second mark should never be hit except in cases where something
actually goes wrong, and for the process test even the 5 second
time should never be reached.  However, for the threaded test we
need to wait the full five seconds to verify that the threads
actually aren't executing concurrently, so this does extend the
runtime of that test even in the success case.  The tests in this
project don't take long though, so having one 10 second test
shouldn't cause anyone too much grief.

I believe an order of magnitude more wait time should be sufficient
to eliminate this bug in any reasonable environment.  I would hope
a given process or thread is not being starved for CPU for more
than 5 seconds in our infra environment, and based on how rarely
this failed even with a .5 second timeout I would expect the
problem to go away completely.

Change-Id: Icfbdc745d129a9028b2c12d0962e4621261ee111
Closes-Bug: 1357582
"}, {'created': '2014-09-10 23:19:57.000000000', 'message': 'Address race in file locking tests

It appears the intermittent failures in the linked bug are caused
by the parent process grabbing the lock after the child has
created the file but before the child has had a chance to lock it.

In order to avoid that happening, wait until the lock has actually
been grabbed, instead of just until the file is created.

This problem does not apply to the threaded test case, and a note
as to why was added in the code.

Change-Id: Icfbdc745d129a9028b2c12d0962e4621261ee111
Closes-Bug: 1357582
'}]
commit_message:
Address race in file locking tests

It appears the intermittent failures in the linked bug are caused
by the parent process grabbing the lock after the child has
created the file but before the child has had a chance to lock it.

In order to avoid that happening, wait until the lock has actually
been grabbed, instead of just until the file is created.

This problem does not apply to the threaded test case, and a note
as to why was added in the code.

Change-Id: Icfbdc745d129a9028b2c12d0962e4621261ee111
Closes-Bug: 1357582

Refactor out duplicate code paths

Use StringBuilder instead of String.
Only touch dimensions once.

Change-Id: Idfe02df5c86874d6fcb1917b2186825f97de6bb6

commit_message:
Fix error adding security groups to instances with nexus

Adding security group to running instance should not
invoke the nexus plugin. Current implementation does not
validate for the 'new_host_id' and assumes it as host migration
and fails. As the nexus monolithic plugin has been removed
after icehouse, this would be merged to stable/icehouse.

Closes-Bug: #1365226

Change-Id: I9ab6b8438e6ee0698a8e2ae7ff7736f7c71b2370

from base class irrespective of safe_setup decorator used or not in
specific test class. Which results to lot of instance of AttributeError
raised from tearDownclass. For example when tests case is skipped.

"}]
commit_message:
Log AttributeError as 'info' instead of 'exception'

When failure happens in setUpClass, tearDownclass is being called
from base class irrespective of safe_setup decorator used or not in
specific test class. Which results to lot of instance of AttributeError
raised from tearDownclass. For example when tests case is skipped.

This patch provides a workaround by logging AttributeError as 'info'
instead of 'exception'.

Permanent fix for cleaning up those in more appropriate way will
be by split-up resource_setup & resource_cleanup in more structural way
as part of second phase of resource cleanup BP.

Change-Id: Ia49c9e171338e22f8d605fc53d251ef3d3471bb1

commit_message:
Fixes a spelling error in hacking tests

commit_message:
libvirt: add _get_launch_flags helper method in unit test

In libvirt driver , we have some logic to generate launch_flags in
method _create_domain_and_network, but in unit test we hard code
launch_flags with '0'. This may lead unit test failure in actual test.
We can't extract the logic to a method in libvirt/driver.py, so add
a helper method with same logic for unit test.

Change-Id: I39ce0162b856daf18488e006b0e424c11811e0c0

commit_message:
consistently set status as REBUILD when rebuilding

Consider an instance is in SHUTOFF status(stopped). When a rebuild
is issued on this instance, the status does not display as REBUILD.

Similarly, when a rebuild is issued on an instance and the operation
fails, the instance turns to ERROR state. Now if we issue a rebuild
again, the status does not display as REBUILD.

This patch fixes the above mentioned issues by displaying the correct
status i.e REBUILD.

Change-Id: Id11c9d31683a049c61fd751dc0ddabaf22c96cb9

We should figure out if the cinder snapshot metadata API actually provides what we need, then we can just expose it via our internal volume API and use it here so we don't have to get the backing volume."}, {'account_id': 6873, 'date': '2014-10-07 14:52:29.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3: -Code-Review

Talking with the Cinder people we got this sorted out.  There is an API to get the snapshot metadata but that's only the metadata provided on the request when the snapshot is created, like instance.metadata.

There is no API to get the volume_image_metadata for a snapshot, and that's what we really want.

So until there is a Cinder API to get at that, we're stuck with getting the volume for the snapshot and then pulling the metadata from that."}, {'account_id': 6873, 'date': '2014-10-07 14:56:58.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: Code-Review+2

commit_message:
Use image metadata from source volume of a snapshot

When booting an instance with the block device mapping V2 API and
source=snapshot, the image metadata is not retrieved and stored in
instance system_metadata.  Metadata is not exposed on a volume snapshot
so it is grabbed from the volume that the snapshot is from.

Change-Id: I96d6c2198b2f94470ab9dfee5e4bddb13992d8d5
Closes-bug: #1375478

commit_message:
Add OSprofiler integration into Heat

This adds builtin rpc and db traces to Heat, as well as
some toplevel stack methods to aid in reading the output.

A 'profiler' config group is added to enable profiling.

Change-Id: Ie5c1c8f1931f59e4d4bcf1ec3b791f55984eb6d2
Closes-bug: #1363782

commit_message:
Add warning to periodic_task with interval 0

In Ia227f4c4e69ecf361ab02d1d17a3010303650104, warnings were
added for several options but instance_delete_interval was
left out by mistake.

Closes-Bug: #1188226

patch removes them. There is another patch against this bug to modify
cinder.

commit_message:
Fix swap_volumes

The attach and detach calls to cinder are better handled by cinder this
patch removes them. There is another patch against this bug to modify
cinder.

The attach call is being made against the new volume after the
migrate_volume_completion request. This means it may be done after the
new volume ID in the db has been deleted.

The detach call is being run at the end on the old ID and so may end up
detaching the migrated volume from cinder's perspective.

Change-Id: I3f2d98e9e473905a3de2f02e00c92ae3065e6ae7
Partial-Bug: 1316079

commit_message:
Fix revoke_cert always raises ProjectNotFound problem

os.chdir will raise OSError if the directory is missing. So
we should catch the OSError instead of checking the return
code from chdir. Add additional checks and tests for checking
directory existence etc.

Closes-bug: #1376368
Change-Id: I9e482cfe19dec1329300fffcf7e51a47d5435724

commit_message:
Update local_settings user group from root to apache

local_settings is set as "root:root" and mode "0640". However
horizon service is running with user "apache" and it needs to read
this file. Hence set its group as "apache".

Fix bug 1370888
Change-Id: I003bef81b7d6b3229af7791dbd4e71936559c5e8

revisions:
[{'created': '2014-06-12 16:52:07.000000000', 'message': "add bash completion script

This patch add a script rally.bash_completion which enables
auto-completion of rally CLI in bash environmnet.

How do we use/test rally bash completion?
1) manually source that file (rally.bash_completion)
2) install bash-completion package, put rally.bash_completion into
/etc/bash_completion.d/ and re-login

TODO:
rally and most of CLIs need the output of '<cmd> bash-completion' which
makes auto-completion smarter. The following job should be enhance the
job 'rally bash-completion' which could support more args and flags.

Change-Id: Ia4c68ccf3faea73da87a93ce64b36545d9d8411c
"}, {'created': '2014-06-12 20:04:03.000000000', 'message': "add bash completion script

This patch add a script rally.bash_completion which enables
auto-completion of rally CLI in bash environmnet when running:

python setup.py install
or
python setup.py develop

TODO:
rally and most of CLIs need the output of '<cmd> bash-completion' which

commit_message:
add bash completion script

This patch add a script rally.bash_completion which enables
auto-completion of rally CLI in bash environmnet when running:

python setup.py install
or
python setup.py develop

test:
rally [tab]
rally ta[tab]
rally task [tab]
rally task de[tab]

to-do:
adding a cache to bash-completion result could speed up auto-completion

Change-Id: Ia4c68ccf3faea73da87a93ce64b36545d9d8411c

commit_message:
Unbreak unit tests for stable/icehouse

This unbreaks unit tests for stable/icehouse by updating tox and
testr config to only run the ironic unit tests and not the in-tree
nova tests, which were never run as part of the gate until Juno.

Change-Id: I39d24470c513e1a328f0b18762bda3e6dec77653

commit_message:
Template not required on stack-adopt

With this change, template is not required on stack-adopt and
also parameters from the original stack are adopted.

Change-Id: Id5a28400bb8e27a3b852f12d9af4c2dc7c144725
Closes-Bug: #1300336
(cherry picked from commit 8c54f483189fef2799357457c3b1e8bc0f9e87c5)

conflicts with the way that the diskimage-builder project

commit_message:
Refactoring IMAGE_TYPE to BASE_IMAGE_OS

Using IMAGE_TYPE to reflect the OS of the base image
conflicts with the way that the diskimage-builder project
uses IMAGE_TYPE (qcow2 vs tar) and was confusing.
We are now using BASE_IMAGE_OS since it properly
reflects what we are using it for and does not conflict
with the diskimage-builder project.

Change-Id: I9e84077c1bc9b8890076838e34a157cb7a3884db
Closes-Bug: #1378364

commit_message:
Make a k8s top level directory for k8s files

k8s (Kubernetes) config json/yaml blobs go in the k8s directory.  This
enables easier addition of base platforms in the docker directory.

Change-Id: I5946a7554770eb14035487080142da7cde380c5e

commit_message:
Delete usage-indications from the model docstrings

I removed some lines from the docstrings in the models due to them
indicating the usage of the function in other parts of the source. This
is not useful as the code could be refactored later, or other usage
could be given to these functions, and thus the comments would become
easily obsolete. Thus, this commit removes them.

Change-Id: I467c8c0a2d7d149e18d2aff87cafb23896bbbca7

[{'created': '2014-10-08 16:03:44.000000000', 'message': 'Install static element files

Several elements want to install static files. Some do this using the
"os-apply-config" directory, which means these files are unnecessarily
rewritten every time os-refresh-config triggers. Others put files in a
"files" dir and manually script the installation from an install.d
script.

This patch offers a more convenient "static" directory. Files placed in
here will be rsynced into the image. This assumes all files are meant to
be installed with user and group root.

Co-Authored-By: Gregory Haynes <greg@greghaynes.net>
Change-Id: I390b822bf80ff6470b25a3473326cac362c4497a
'}]
commit_message:
Install static element files

Several elements want to install static files. Some do this using the
"os-apply-config" directory, which means these files are unnecessarily
rewritten every time os-refresh-config triggers. Others put files in a
"files" dir and manually script the installation from an install.d
script.

This patch offers a more convenient "static" directory. Files placed in
here will be rsynced into the image. This assumes all files are meant to
be installed with user and group root.

Co-Authored-By: Gregory Haynes <greg@greghaynes.net>
Change-Id: I390b822bf80ff6470b25a3473326cac362c4497a

commit_message:
XenServer: Add XenServer support

Upstreaming several changes from XenServer CI:
 - Use tty0 as console - thus the user can see what's happening during
   installation over VNC console.
 - Set the number of VCPUs to 6 for the DomU appliance
 - Add prepare_node_xenserver.sh script.
 - Use testing xva 1.1.4 which has trusty.

Change-Id: I56fc4e1af12f3f13fd1aa0b772bd8734b412d3d5

commit_message:
Fix AttributeError in admin_cleanup

There will be an AttributeError in admin_cleanup when the user has no
tenant attached.

commit_message:
Modify rabbitmq pod to point to right image

The image location for rabbitmq was incorrectly pointing at Lars
private repository.  Change it to point to the global kollaglue repo.

[{'created': '2014-09-24 10:24:34.000000000', 'message': "VMware: Set vmPathName properly in fake driver

When creating a VM, we pass in config.files.vmPathName as '[ds]'.
However, when this value is subsequently retrieved from a real vSphere
server, it is '[ds] uuid/uuid.vmx'.

This change defaults the value of vmPathName if it's a bare datastore
name to mirror the behaviour of a real vSphere server.

Change-Id: Ide2a4d69fe0ce3214c85b132a8d653f8d5e275f9

commit_message:
VMware: Set vmPathName properly in fake driver

When creating a VM, we pass in config.files.vmPathName as '[ds]'.
However, when this value is subsequently retrieved from a real vSphere
server, it is '[ds] uuid/uuid.vmx'.

This change defaults the value of vmPathName if it's a bare datastore
name to mirror the behaviour of a real vSphere server.

Change-Id: Ide2a4d69fe0ce3214c85b132a8d653f8d5e275f9

commit_message:
Use ID for namespace generated by DB

In current implementation ID that is used in namespace to
insert data to DB is generated by built-in function - enumerate.
This causes problems with loading the metadata when there are already
namespaces in DB.

This patch removes 'enumerate' and asks for namespace ID
generated by database.

Closes-Bug: #1367771
Co-Authored-By: Bartosz Fic <bartosz.fic@intel.com>
Co-Authored-By: Pawel Koniszewski <pawel.koniszewski@intel.com>
(cherry picked from commit 89c04904416270d3c306d430f443a7127c5fc206)

Conflicts:
	glance/db/sqlalchemy/metadata.py

Change-Id: I235c6310077526cafb898ac007c3601b4d66c9fe

commit_message:
Metadef Property and Object schema columns should use JSONEncodedDict

The MetadefProperty and MetadefObject ORM classes currently specify the
JSON schema columns as type Text. It is preferred to use the
JSONEncodedDict Type Decorator instead. This fix also includes necessary
code changes to remove JSON encoding/decoding that was previously done
in other layers. Fixes for unit tests involving the schema columns are
also included.

Closes-Bug: 1368479

Conflicts:
	glance/db/__init__.py
	glance/db/sqlalchemy/models_metadef.py

Change-Id: I2c574210f8d62c77a438afab83ff80f3e5bd2fe7
(cherry picked from commit 824d9620b0b90483baf45981d2cb328855943e06)

commit_message:
IBM Storwize driver: Retype the volume with correct empty QoS

* Currently for Storwzie driver, if the new type does not have QoS
configurations, the old QoS configurations remain in the volume after
retyping it. It should be retyped into a volume with empty QoS for the
Storwize driver.
* Refactor three dicts into one for better maintainance of the QoS keys
for Storwize driver.

DocImpact

Change-Id: I2b2801a4ef72ef02c11392ed00b56f5263a8a7e4
Closes-Bug: #1368595
(cherry picked from commit 26de1b1d829849665dae921b8be739194b84515d)

ZFSSA iSCSI driver cannot add multple initiators to a group

All initiators defined in zfssa_initiator property would be
added to the group.

[{'created': '2014-10-08 10:28:34.000000000', 'message': 'Fix race condition in ISCSIConnector _disconnect_volume_multipath_iscsi

This is a similar issue as seen in
https://bugs.launchpad.net/cinder/+bug/1375382

The list of devices returned by driver.get_all_block_devices() in
_disconnect_volume_multipath_iscsi will potentially contain broken
symlinks as the SCSI devices have been deleted from calling
self._linuxscsi.remove_multipath_device(device_realpath) right before
_disconnect_volume_multipath_iscsi but the udev rule for the symlink
may not yet have completed.

Adding in a check to os.path.exists() will ensure that we will not
consider the broken symlinks as an “in use” device.

Change-Id: I79c9627e9b47127d3765fcec5b7e3bacef179630
Closes-Bug: #1375946
(cherry picked from commit 4541521de576297d9b7d4115b040ff54773d9d50)
'}]
commit_message:
Fix race condition in ISCSIConnector _disconnect_volume_multipath_iscsi

This is a similar issue as seen in
https://bugs.launchpad.net/cinder/+bug/1375382

The list of devices returned by driver.get_all_block_devices() in
_disconnect_volume_multipath_iscsi will potentially contain broken
symlinks as the SCSI devices have been deleted from calling
self._linuxscsi.remove_multipath_device(device_realpath) right before
_disconnect_volume_multipath_iscsi but the udev rule for the symlink
may not yet have completed.

Adding in a check to os.path.exists() will ensure that we will not
consider the broken symlinks as an “in use” device.

Change-Id: I79c9627e9b47127d3765fcec5b7e3bacef179630
Closes-Bug: #1375946
(cherry picked from commit 4541521de576297d9b7d4115b040ff54773d9d50)

commit_message:
Deprecate / obsolete NetApp volume extra specs

The NetApp Data ONTAP (Cluster-mode) NFS & iSCSI drivers for Juno support
the Cinder pools feature, but the drivers are reporting two qualified
extra specs that must be converted to unqualified extra specs in order to
be used by the Cinder scheduler's capability filter. Furthermore, there
are four extra specs that must be deprecated due to having the pools
feature.  Warnings will be logged during volume creation if any of the
obsolete or deprecated extra specs are seen in the volume type.

Change-Id: I4dbd667610e481356304a12b8dae84cff61aa9d9
Closes-bug: 1374630
(cherry picked from commit 4cb4be4122a44dc99d6f29f065cdd32ae86273ce)

commit_message:
setup.py requires pbr

revisions:
[{'created': '2014-10-06 11:54:21.000000000', 'message': "Move marker field to the first position (index)

This patch moves the marker field `k` to the top-most position of the
`MARKER_INDEX_FIELDS` compound index. This change improves the index in
2 ways:

1. It'll start filtering for messages starting with marker `k`. This is
good because the probability of having millions of messages with the
same marker is lower than having millions of messages for the same
project. This means fewer index records will need to be scanned to get
the messages.

2. This key will be used as a shard-key because it brings enough
cardinality to ensure chunks are evenly distributed and it also ensures
uniqueness of markers per p_q

Change-Id: I13d3773f7e5a2835f4d57a0e27b5dad221234028
"}]
commit_message:
Move marker field to the first position (index)

This patch moves the marker field `k` to the top-most position of the
`MARKER_INDEX_FIELDS` compound index. This change improves the index in
2 ways:

1. It'll start filtering for messages starting with marker `k`. This is
good because the probability of having millions of messages with the
same marker is lower than having millions of messages for the same
project. This means fewer index records will need to be scanned to get
the messages.

2. This key will be used as a shard-key because it brings enough
cardinality to ensure chunks are evenly distributed and it also ensures
uniqueness of markers per p_q

Change-Id: I13d3773f7e5a2835f4d57a0e27b5dad221234028

commit_message:
Remove baremetal virt driver

This patch removes the baremetal virt driver from nova, which was
deprecated in Juno. It does not aim to perform any of the refactoring
we need to do now that the driver is gone, but is intended as a clean
removal of all the baremetal code itself.

Of specific note are the api_samples tests. We didn't have samples to
test the ironic proxy code, so I removed the baremetal ones for show
and index, resetting that extension back to "untested" status as if it
was new.

Tests that stub out ironic interactions and re-introduce those tests
should be added after this patch.

Change-Id: Ia76e41a8a3b7230701872ae7a1975edc3d9ea847

commit_message:
Add support for redis-sentinel

This patch adds the ability to configure Sentinel support in
zaqar.conf. The code has been tested using one and two sentinels
managing one master and one slave. Failovers from master to slave
were intiated and it was verified that clients can continue to
query the service with no downtime in the case of a lost Redis
node.

Co-Authored-By: Kurt Griffiths <kurt.griffiths@rackspace.com>
Closes-Bug: 1367020
Change-Id: Idcaaab3ba17c84a31b918ad8376f1d5fc105b53a

commit_message:
Extends COMMIT parameters with git hash in make system

We can define the exact commit hash or branch that
want to use for building packages from.

Value should be defined in config.mk with format:
 REPONAME_COMMIT?=branch
  or
 REPONAME_COMMIT?=hash
for example:
 FUELLIB_COMMIT?=stable/5.1
 FUELLIB_COMMIT?=203ef3179007cffe3236032e61ecbaf1cd20605f

Change-Id: Ifa225003f03dfa41028abb6db0a5ac83ad22f81e
Close-bug: #1364076

commit_message:
Rework autoscaling group current_size attribute

The current implementation requires a path which is not needed.
rsrc.FnGetAtt('current_size', 'name')
it should allow:
rsrc.FnGetAtt('current_size')

Also move the tests to the correct test module and make them more
into unit tests.

Change-Id: Id05a1f09ecc6741cbf677baf52fbb58d93028ac4

Due to a bug in python < 2.7.4, urlparse won't parse a query string

Commit 1dda5ef75a5c141c316639716820b0c37773a9e3 added some tests for

proxy console URLs do not support the websocket protocol scheme (ws://)

commit_message:
console: make unsupported ws scheme in python < 2.7.4

Due to a bug in python < 2.7.4, urlparse won't parse a query string
in a URL where the scheme is not recognized:

http://bugs.python.org/issue9374

Commit 1dda5ef75a5c141c316639716820b0c37773a9e3 added some tests for
websocketproxy that uses urlparse to get a token but these don't work
on python < 2.7.4 since the scheme in the tests is "ws://".

In the actual code, raise an exception if python < 2.7.4 and an
unsupported URL scheme is used.

DocImpact: The "getting-started-with-vnc-proxy" page in the
"admin-guide-cloud" docs should be updated with a note that the web
proxy console URLs do not support the websocket protocol scheme (ws://)
on python versions less than 2.7.4.

Change-Id: Ib6e0fc4e50c1ea144a9c538099e23597d66b429b
Closes-Bug: #1376078

commit_message:
ZFSSA iSCSI vol create fails with vol type option

Vol create with volume-type option is not working since
volume_backend_name contains the class name as
predefined string. No matter what was specified in cinder.conf
as volume_backend_name, volume creation failed.
Multi-backend option and using extra specs to create custom volumes
won't work.
The fix is to look whether volume_backend_name is part of the
configuration or falls into the class name in case there is
no backend name.

Closes-Bug: 1373621
DocImpact

(cherry picked from commit 5c61d57d3693523e9cbf11bf0b5b09bafe699247)

Change-Id: I1bc501dd4c5689d96c7beb720b64112df1770232

commit_message:
GET property which name includes resource type prefix

Currently GET call to API to retrieve property details ends with
404 error when property name includes resource type prefix.
This patch extends show method to take filters as a parameter.
If 'resource_type' is included in filters then the prefix of included
resource type is removed from property name. This enables user to look
for property name starting with prefix that comes from associated
resource type.

Change-Id: I3c4d96fbc9ce15016631017bf76089c338ac3cdc
Closes-Bug: #1367564
DocImpact
Co-Authored-By: Bartosz Fic <bartosz.fic@intel.com>
Co-Authored-By: Pawel Koniszewski <pawel.koniszewski@intel.com>

commit_message:
Grab the html version of console log

Currently we are only grabbing the text output from Jenkins. However,
this doesn't have timestamps which isn't ideal. We can use the
internal url that is used by Jenkins to generate its web page to
fetch the console logs with timestamps and formatting.

This is the update for the jenkins macros.
Co-Authored-By: Joshua Hesketh <josh@nitrotech.org>

Change-Id: I1a092514cbc4e29d783dd120c69cc15f32885b48

commit_message:
Update shares and snapshot create to show details

This patch has POST responses for share and snapshot creates return a full
detailed representation of the resource instead of a summary response.

Change-Id: I96cb7ade490f39ca1f1da7faecd2b6a8e23608fd

commit_message:
Fix some LOG.debug invocations

LOG.debug("Hello %s" % xyz) should be LOG.debug("Hello %s", xyz).
This allows the logging package to skip creating the
formatted log message if the message is not going to be emitted because
of the current log level.

Change-Id: Ie0c91cd940017fd80d1d84b0e56780a1da980858

commit_message:
Fix tempest compatibility

Decorator "safe_setup" was removed in Tempest project, we need to remove its
usage to fix compatibility.

Gerrit commit: https://review.openstack.org/#/c/122531/
Tempest commit: https://github.com/openstack/tempest/commit/c27feb85

Change-Id: I1c9a9a668b3d7761c07af72aff8415b86ffaa8a5
Closes-Bug: #1378677

commit_message:
Add temp files of vim and cover tox job to .gitignore file

Without this change git considers temp files of vim and cover tox job as new
files, so add them to .gitignore.

Change-Id: Id1f7b2785b928dedd00f0848aad7ad81718699eb

commit_message:
Fix AttributeError when trying to get tenantId

If keystone v2 user have no default tenant, then User object
have no tenantId attribute at all

Change-Id: Icda61222002860ff04739c6e18537ba832bebeb9
Closes-Bug: 1378873

commit_message:
Make v2.1 API tests use v2 URLs(test_[a-e].*)

Most v2.1 API tests are using v3 URLs, because there didn't exist
a fake router for v2.1 at the time. However, now the fake router
exists.
This makes v2.1 API tests of use v2 URLs for testing v2.1 API as
v2 compatible API for test_[a-e].*.py.

Partially implements blueprint v2-on-v3-api

Change-Id: I9b5901ca294d10a9ded52603f9cc46155b07009d

commit_message:
Fix for Adopt glance.store library in Glance

The store module is removed from glance project and new glance_store
module is created, but the glance project code was not updated
properly for the required changes.

The exception (UnknownScheme) was moved to glance_store, but in
glance image-create api (v1), it still refers to
exception.UnknownScheme in get_store_or_400 method.

Change-Id: I09e78b92d2d44a659412361b4f03b4a988714bf5
Closes-Bug: 1373454

commit_message:
Remove templates from toctrees

We don't want the templates to show up in the RSS feed, so exclude them
from being converted to HTML and listed in the toctree.

Change-Id: I1d50944fc37f27b5fc67316270cb281e3635b762

commit_message:
Add nsenter container

Because nsenter is not available in
CentOS 6.5, it can be obtained from a
container jpetazzo/nsenter. This is
necessary for running Docker with
the native exec driver.

blueprint fuel-master-docker-host-networking

Change-Id: I1c13abf94ecd41de22f08c633dc1d91377167fda

the condition and go on.  This is harmless since it can happen

commit_message:
Don't fail when trying to unbind a router

If a router is already unbound from an l3 agent, don't fail.  Log
the condition and go on.  This is harmless since it can happen
due to a delete race condition between multiple neutron-server
processes.  One delete request can determine that it needs to
unbind the router.  A second process may also determine that it
needs to unbind the router.  The exception thrown will result
in a port delete failure and cause nova to mark a deleted instance
as ERROR.

Change-Id: Ia667ea77a0a483deff8acfdcf90ca84cd3adf44f
Closes-Bug: 1367892

commit_message:
Return empty string instead of None (systests)

In 'execute_through_host' method return empty string if
exception is caught. This is required to avoid type errors
in tests which use that function. Also, increase log level
to 'error' for message about occurred exception.

Change-Id: I7021ee90e32f39b2183b7693d3ba6fe4c669517d
Closes-bug: #1369962
(cherry picked from commit 10195ef8622c6ff3366c679d6bcfe9939635f496)

commit_message:
Move database fixture to a separate test case

This change moves database fixture from ironic.tests.base.TestCase to
ironic.tests.db.base.DbTestCase and adds dbapi field there. Also it
adds ironic admin context to ironic.tests.base.TestCase, as context
may be used without db fixture.

Closes-bug: #1376285

Change-Id: I008e44da315767afb6282000a01f0b39698f9768

commit_message:
Reorganization of gating setup

Reorganize the gating setup to combine the tiny jobs into a single
voting and a single non-voting check. This will give more flexibility
in adding new jobs and reduce load of Jenkins.

bp reorg-gating

Change-Id: I2abda19804e6fb115244c5c54e4570a57fd326f8

commit_message:
Removing default '' return for ast_args_to_str()

This removes a default return value for ast_args_to_str() that was
an development stub artifact.  Additional work may be needed to clean
this function up but will leave it returning something for now.

Change-Id: I99904a49358097728de27051bae65791822f2f3e

commit_message:
Return empty string instead of None (systests)

In 'execute_through_host' method return empty string if
exception is caught. This is required to avoid type errors
in tests which use that function. Also, increase log level
to 'error' for message about occurred exception.

Change-Id: I7021ee90e32f39b2183b7693d3ba6fe4c669517d
Closes-bug: #1369962

commit_message:
Mask passwords in exceptions and error messages

When a ProcessExecutionError is thrown by processutils.ssh_execute(),
the exception may contain information such as password. Upstream
applications that just log the message (as several appear to do)
could inadvertently expose these passwords to a user with read access to
the log files. It is therefore considered prudent to invoke
strutils.mask_password() on the command, stdout and stderr in the
exception. A test case has been added (to oslo-incubator) in order to 
ensure that all three are properly masked.

An earlier commit (853d8f9897f8563851441108a9be26b10908c076) failed
to address ssh_execute(). This change set addresses ssh_execute.

OSSA is aware of this change request.

Change-Id: Ie0caf32469126dd9feb44867adf27acb6e383958
Closes-Bug: #1377981

commit_message:
Update rpc version aliases for juno

Update all of the rpc client API classes to include a version alias
for the latest version implemented in Juno.  This alias is needed when
doing rolling upgrades from Juno to Kilo.  With this in place, you can
ensure all services only send messages that both Juno and Kilo will
understand.

Closes-bug: #1378786
Change-Id: Ia81538130bf8530b70b5f55c7a3d565903ff54b4
(cherry picked from commit f98d725103c53e767a1cddb0b7e2c3822309db17)

commit_message:
Correct a maybe-typo in pci_manager

the variable 'dev' in set_hvdevs are only used for list comprehension,
it does not make sense to use 'dev' again for updating self.stale.

Change-Id: I03f31bfcfc56a43e43eb88845e1d562f19a3a09e

commit_message:
Move volume_clear option to where it's used

The `volume_clear` and `volume_clear_size` option are used in `lvm.py` so we
should move the definition there.

Change-Id: Ic619c2db0bb1b5ccc7dcbec1a500c3dcb1110b26

revisions:
[{'created': '2014-08-08 21:28:07.000000000', 'message': "object-ify flavors

This change converts flavors to use the Flavor object instead of
direct database access.

This means that the Instance object will now have a Flavor object
as its instance_type instead of a dict. The instance_type inside of
a request_spec, however, remains a dict as it seems request_spec is
intended to be a flat dict object.

Another note is that filter_properties must be converted to a
primitive before sending over RPC as it now has a Flavor object
stored at its instance_type dict key. Once NovaObjectSerializer
can recursively serialize/deserialize objects inside of dicts,
it won't have to be done manually.

Related to blueprint compute-manager-objects-juno

Change-Id: I0082a56aa637169fd6e1db3aad56877c9f745bc5
"}, {'created': '2014-08-12 06:13:19.000000000', 'message': "object-ify flavors

get_flavor_by_flavor_id().

Don't raise 500 on carbonara NoDeloreanAvailable

If the API user post outdated measures we must return a 400 error,
not a 500.

commit_message:
Update NoMoreFixedIps message description

The exception NoMoreFixedIps within Nova is a generic exception.
It is used to indicate that the subnets within the network no longer
have any available fixed IPs for use.

The original message was non specific.  This change set provides an
updated message that indicates which network has exhausted its fixed
IP set.

This is important for operators that are deploying instances with
multiple networks.

Change-Id: Ib8b854381b616f83e82bc573f85e109f019897dc
Closes-Bug: #1366982

[{'created': '2014-10-07 15:24:55.000000000', 'message': 'Mask passwords in exceptions and error messages

When a ProcessExecutionError is thrown by processutils.ssh_execute(),
the exception may contain information such as password. Upstream
applications that just log the message (as several appear to do)
could inadvertently expose these passwords to a user with read access to
the log files. It is therefore considered prudent to invoke

exception. A test case has been added (to oslo-incubator) in order to

Closes-Bug: #1377981
'}]
commit_message:
Mask passwords in exceptions and error messages

When a ProcessExecutionError is thrown by processutils.ssh_execute(),
the exception may contain information such as password. Upstream
applications that just log the message (as several appear to do)
could inadvertently expose these passwords to a user with read access to
the log files. It is therefore considered prudent to invoke
strutils.mask_password() on the command, stdout and stderr in the
exception. A test case has been added (to oslo-incubator) in order to 
ensure that all three are properly masked.

An earlier commit (853d8f9897f8563851441108a9be26b10908c076) failed
to address ssh_execute(). This change set addresses ssh_execute.

OSSA is aware of this change request.

Change-Id: Ie0caf32469126dd9feb44867adf27acb6e383958
Closes-Bug: #1377981

commit_message:
libvirt: Fix kwargs for _create_image

Rescue uses the `suffix` and `disk_images` kwargs of `_create_image`, but
passes them in as positional args. We should use explicit kwargs here to be
clear that rescue depends on both of those parameters being present.

In addition, disk mapping was being passed in as kwarg, but is actually a
positional arg, so we should pass it in as a positional arg to be clear that
it's required.

Change-Id: Iaa990729b4bb3569f4c71ceaf1adabed58f73026

commit_message:
Default to system CA bundle if no CA certificate is provided

If no CA certificate is provided to be used for validation then
fall back to the system-wide CA bundle as presented by
python-requests.

Change-Id: I05206a868150d4b62b6f1b833310eb9b86b7c4f8
Closes-bug: #1362179

commit_message:
API level refactoring

Now we have 2 API - REST and DynamoDB.
But both of those 2 APIs are implemented in single WSGI application
Now it becomes to be a problem for future features implementation

This patch separates tese 2 API on paste configuration level

Change-Id: Icf4edc5647f3a0fa5b87b51b133939a77d35ff97

commit_message:
baremetal: Remove depenency on libvirt's fetch_image method

It's messy for virt-drivers to depend on each other, so this patch alters
baremetal to use the cross-driver fetch function, instead of the libvirt
version.

Change-Id: I910c621452fa7eb9add417a8738e5757aeb1a48c

commit_message:
Port fping extension to work in v2.1/v3 framework

Ports v2 fping extension and adapts it to the v2.1/v3 API
framework. API behaviour is identical.

- unittest code modified to share testing with both v2/v2.1
- Adds expected error decorators for API methods

Partially implements blueprint v2-on-v3-api

Change-Id: I8dc4ede46826bf6062097a3b4ba6be9a09a1bd12

Passthrough-enable ceilometer.conf

This permits passthrough settings to be applied to ceilometer.conf using
'ceilometer' as the key in the config.

commit_message:
Add cookie-based authentication along with X-Auth-Token

- added jquery.cookie as Bower dependency
- fixed keystone.py middleware to process the cookie and inject X-Auth-Token
  into the request, X-Auth-Token still has priority though
- fixed 401 response format to return iterable (list)
- added test_auth_token for testing both authentication methods

Change-Id: I01239c93b8f0d5da95424d44c96f6fb60ab378fd
Implements: blueprint access-control-master-node-improvments

children.  Python 3 sets the O_CLOEXEC flag on the file descriptor
by default so this doesn't happen.  Because of the Python 2
behavior, our test code explicitly closes the file descriptor in

tests still run fine, and with that done the py3 tests no longer
have a problem either.  This is fortunate because if the py2
behavior allowed multiple processes to hold the lock at once it
would obviously be a Bad Thing. :-)

commit_message:
Handle Python 3's O_CLOEXEC default

In Python 2, a file opened by a process was inherited by all of its
children.  Python 3 sets the O_CLOEXEC flag on the file descriptor
by default so this doesn't happen.  Because of the Python 2
behavior, our test code explicitly closes the file descriptor in
one test, but we shouldn't be doing that since it wouldn't happen
in a real usage scenario.

Fortunately, it appears both cases work in a sane fashion anyway.
With the explicit release removed from the child process, the py2
tests still run fine, and with that done the py3 tests no longer
have a problem either.  This is fortunate because if the py2
behavior allowed multiple processes to hold the lock at once it
would obviously be a Bad Thing. :-)

Change-Id: I133334dee068984b1309180c5338ac19d9934274

commit_message:
Use getLogger(__name__)

The variable __name__ should be preferred over hardcoded names
to reference the used logging object.

Moved some calls to the root scope and removed unused LOG variables
and logging imports.

Kept hardoced names in nova/cmd and only moved calls to the root scope.

Change-Id: Id1161bd0fafe7a425c40e426cb43a2d22277e00a

commit_message:
Use versions in paths to repos/puppets

Since Fuel 5.0 we support fuel upgrades and the old approach (storing
repos/puppets without version prefix) do not work anymore.

Change-Id: I26c69f7d03b9bd86a8b50841b46d2dada030b235

[{'created': '2014-07-04 07:38:08.000000000', 'message': 'Initial Commit

nova net-delete of associated network is not informative enough

Fix:

Intially nova net-delete <Network ID> was raising an
"InternalServerError - ERROR: The server has either erred or is
incapable of performing the requested operation. (HTTP 500) (Request-ID
: <req_id>)", in case the requested network to delete was associated to
any project.

This error category “Internal Server Error” is appropriate but the
error message description is not informative enough.

Now, when the command is not able to delete the requested network because
it is associated with a project, a message stating “network must be
disassociated from project <project-id> before delete” will be raised.
Updated the code to raise the new error message.

close the bug.

Change-Id: I692e8ab105ae03f485f4cef01021d5bbe5036388

commit_message:
nova net-delete of associated network is not informative enough

Fix:

Intially nova net-delete <Network ID> was raising an
"InternalServerError - ERROR: The server has either erred or is
incapable of performing the requested operation. (HTTP 500) (Request-ID
: <req_id>)", in case the requested network to delete was associated to
any project.

This error category “Internal Server Error” is appropriate but the
error message description is not informative enough.

Now, when the command is not able to delete the requested network because
it is associated with a project, a message stating “network must be
disassociated from project <project-id> before delete” will be raised.
Updated the code to raise the new error message.

Closes-Bug: 1301373 .

Change-Id: I692e8ab105ae03f485f4cef01021d5bbe5036388

commit_message:
g-api raises 500 error while uploading image

If both filesystem_store_datadirs and filesystem_store_datadir parameters
specified in glance-api.conf file then while creating new image 500
internal server error is raised.

Caught StoreAddDisabled exception for v1 and v2 api while uploading
image and raised HTTPGone exception to return HTTP 410 response to
user.

Closes-Bug: #1372888
Change-Id: Iccbf5b88634d3c956d41e8d8a0126648c64b34eb

Any exception thrown by spawn is irrelevant to this test as long as it
doesn't interfere with the scrubbed log message being generated. The
change being reverted makes the test more fragile to unrelated code
change without providing any benefits.

This reverts commit 0110cd7c0da1ba42df891f1d61e9dc2f2e7fe42b.

Change-Id: Ifcbd4d2607665e4072b77f3ca10ffd3159f0d0b1
'}]
commit_message:
Revert "Avoid using except Exception in unit test"

Any exception thrown by spawn is irrelevant to this test as long as it
doesn't interfere with the scrubbed log message being generated. The
change being reverted makes the test more fragile to unrelated code
change without providing any benefits.

This reverts commit 0110cd7c0da1ba42df891f1d61e9dc2f2e7fe42b.

Change-Id: Ifcbd4d2607665e4072b77f3ca10ffd3159f0d0b1

This patch breaks alarm creation for me. It happens because when we collect all properties we add also in kwargs MATCHING_METADATA. It's not required prop, but according to [1] this value should be dict (otherwise will be error from six.iteritems), but if it's not presented in template it will be None. So you will get error during creation:
AttributeError: 'NoneType' object has no attribute 'iteritems' 

[1] https://github.com/openstack/heat/blob/master/heat/engine/resources/ceilometer/alarm.py#L181-L191"}, {'account_id': 6577, 'date': '2014-10-06 13:21:10.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

I think, that as solution you may exclude all values with None value, at the end of actions_to_urls function.'}, {'account_id': 4715, 'date': '2014-10-07 01:05:47.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2:

Sergey thanks for catching that. I think the right solution is to have correct defaults. If we don't send None for some properties you won't be able to reset things to their defaults. I'll try just adding a default of {} for matching_metadata and see how that works."}, {'account_id': 4715, 'date': '2014-10-07 01:41:07.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 3.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2014-10-07 02:38:10.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: Verified-1

commit_message:
Use properties in ceilometer alarm not parsed_template('Properties')

The main point of this patch is to pass the default values defined
in the property schema into ceilometer.

Closes-bug: #1375151
Change-Id: Icfc917a02c2e6404213ec020a9aba24fcbb4168a

commit_message:
Make sure that property defaults are converted correctly

If a developer defines a default boolean as "true", then we really want
True when we do "self.properties['bla']" not 'true', otherwise this
is not consistent.

Change-Id: I3705e573e2fd68a04b26c5589d38f84d68641738
Partial-bug: #1375151

commit_message:
Use oslo.utils

oslo.utils library now provides the functionality previously in
oslo-incubator's excutils, importutils, network_utils, strutils
timeutils, units etc. Some modules already moved to oslo.utils
will still be around since other code in nova/openstack/common/
are using it and will be removed in a subsequent commit.

Change-Id: Idc716342535fdfa680963e0e073ddb46f5f1eb34

commit_message:
Incorrect parameters passed

Incorrect parameters sequence is passed to
delete_from_backend() method.

delete_from_backend(self.admin_context, uri) in this
method uri should be the first argument instead of
self.admin_context.

Closes-Bug:1378640
Change-Id: Iebc30bad4f201dde75f2e8fe9b56e20c007c772b

It's ugly, but I think we *must* update the vmrc console driver. It's activated by a config option (console_driver), which is why it isn't directly referenced by other code. It calls vim_session._get_vim() in generate_password(). vim_session is created in vmrc_manager.py as a VMwareAPISession object, so there's no question that we would break it if anybody was using it.

The fact that there don't appear to be any tests for this driver is obviously bad, and makes me suspect that it would no longer work anyway. Also, fixing that isn't the concern of this patch. commit_message:
VMware: remove _get_vim() from VMwareAPISession

This method has side-effects which are not needed and brings only
clutter in the driver. The vim object should be accessed as a standard
property of the session object.
This patch is mostly a mechanical replacement and doesn't change any
existing functionality.

This is part of blueprint use-oslo-vmware

Change-Id: I1e86a2e5afc5c0b5921c0248806f434df0cdef2a

commit_message:
Add missing metadefs for shutdown behavior

The following Nova patch adds support for graceful shutdown
of a guest VM and allows setting timeout properties on images.
The properties should be updated in the Metadata Definitions catalog.

https://review.openstack.org/#/c/68942/

Change-Id: I58145d9d0114b3932b63263ea123c4662146d14b
Closes-bug: 1368036
(cherry picked from commit 5fcb3aa2e35e9af17cb8be9e24c6613626036f2b)

commit_message:
Closes-Bug: 1291111
Closes-Bug: 1322200
Problem:
=======
When devstack is installed behind a proxy with proxy variables
http_proxy and https_proxy being exported and without exporting
no_proxy, the installation will fail. The reason is that any REST
request sent to Keystone will be redirected to the proxy server.
Solution:
========
Fix involves appending no_proxy variable with localhost,HOST_IP,
SERVICE_HOST if they are not included already and then exporting
the variable.

Save it into localrc.

commit_message:
Task arguments changed

To avoid failures of fuelclient code because of ambiguity of arguments
supplying, arguments declaration for task operation changed to more
obvious scheme.

Change-Id: I58d0b4a5245d15bcb7f4ff28c8048ebad39e43e2
Closes-Bug: #1364007

commit_message:
Fixes live-migration failed because of cpu features duplication

- Use a tmp list to check cpu-features duplication.
- This check should be done in nova/virt/libvirt/driver.py
  because not easy to check in nova/virt/libvirt/config.py

Closes-Bug: #1319710
Change-Id: I1b44e0f1a766c0b250ee2c1272b344cfd1498eee

commit_message:
Fix hourly log rotation schedule

W/o this patch, new log rotation template for
Fuel 5.x master node with docker (which is
/etc/logrotate.d/20-fuel-docker.conf) would
never be scheduled for execution.
And that could have caused master node's /var/log/
free space exhausted until the next planned daily
log rotation will come.

DocImpact
Closes-bug: #1378327

Change-Id: I21ba3debcfda4d94d5e25786f97996f6431e5ec3
Signed-off-by: Bogdan Dobrelya <bdobrelia@mirantis.com>

commit_message:
KeyError from AgentVendorInterface._heartbeat()

A KeyError exception could be raised in AgentVendorInterface._heartbeat()
if kwargs['agent_url'] doesn't exist. It *should* always exist, but just
in case, reraising a MissingParameterValue exception with a more specific
msg would be helpful in debugging.

Change-Id: I5e7971e7e8062d7917cc34eb9e0178778ed5035a
Closes-Bug: #1378440

cmd init_node [-n <node_name>]

'}]
commit_message:
labs: add options for config cmds

This patch adds two options to configuration commands (config/scripts.*).

-n <node_name>: change target node of command
-g <gui_type>: override GUI type (gui, headless, sdl) for this boot

The changed syntax is as follows:

cmd boot [-g <gui_type>] [-n <node_name>]
cmd snapshot [-n <node_name>] <snapshot_name>
cmd wait_for_shutdown [-n <node_name>]
cmd snapshot_cycle [-g <gui_type>] [-n <node_name>]
cmd init_node [-n <node_name>]

Change-Id: Id2673c6d504aed33f0259d5751084442e851684b

commit_message:
Manually updated translations

The workflow boils down to:

 $ sudo easy_install Babel
 $ sudo yum install gettext
 $ python setup.py extract_messages
 $ python setup.py update_catalog --no-fuzzy-matching \
   --ignore-obsolete=true
 $ source \
   ../project-config/jenkins/scripts/common_translation_update.sh
 $ setup_loglevel_vars
 $ cleanup_po_files ceilometer

Change-Id: Ia16b2b15004e0e0cbd4332ed5106ba04f1736ade

commit_message:
Add ':' inside translatable (Part 2 of 2)

Punctuation needs to be included in translation since punctuation differs
depending on the language.  Along with moving ':' also replaced   with
blank space insde trans or transblock tag.The initial review grew too large,
so this patch has been broken into 2 reviews.  Part 2 will cover the files in
openstack_dashboard/dashboard/project while Part 1 coverered the rest.

Change-Id: Ibf2036d5bbc4c478fcb912f6335104356e8f1317
Partially-Closes-Bug: #1369445

commit_message:
Sprinkle :: throughout the setup-neutron docs

Force the setup-neutron section of usage.rst into line by using ::
to tell ReST that the following paragraph is a code block, which
makes it match the rest of the document.

commit_message:
Use ID for namespace generated by DB

In current implementation ID that is used in namespace to
insert data to DB is generated by built-in function - enumerate.
This causes problems with loading the metadata when there are already
namespaces in DB.

This patch removes 'enumerate' and asks for namespace ID
generated by database.

Change-Id: I235c6310077526cafb898ac007c3601b4d66c9fe
Closes-Bug: #1367771
Co-Authored-By: Bartosz Fic <bartosz.fic@intel.com>
Co-Authored-By: Pawel Koniszewski <pawel.koniszewski@intel.com>

commit_message:
Suppressed misleading log in unshelve, resize api

If instance is booted from volume, unshelve and
resize instance unnecessarily logs 'image not found'
error and warning messages in the compute.log when
image_id_or_uri is passed as None to
nova/compute/utils->get_image_metadata method.

To avoid this error and warning message, calling
image_api.get() method only if image_id_or_uri is
not 'None'.

Closes-Bug: #1370019
Change-Id: Ibf8c02fa153fc096e4e8a1c054ef62c935006091

(151 comments)

So, I have gone through the code in patch set 16.  Hopefully there weren't too many changes with the additional patch sets you uploaded.

Overall comments:  I think the level of logging and error checking is good.  Lots to work with on a running system.  Also, I think the comments in the code are good.  In many places there is good help understanding what is going on.

The things that need to be addressed:
- Don't use str(), need to use six.text_type.
- Don't use LOG.warn ... logging standards document LOG.warning and we should be using that.
- There are a couple of places I think we need to look at using loopingcall instead of just sleeping in the code where we could block up the volume service.
- Comments to make logging format consistent.
- Do not concatenate exceptions on to log messages.  This can actually cause exceptions in the logging code.
- Fix the _ imports to use cinder.i18n.

I think that covers the major themes.  Let me know if you have any questions.

Thanks!"}, {'account_id': 7198, 'date': '2014-08-20 14:30:10.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 18: Code-Review-1

* FAST policies

commit_message:
EMC VMAX Driver Juno Update

This driver is an enhancement from the EMC SMI-S driver.
In Juno, VNX support will be removed from this driver.
Moving forward, this driver will support VMAX only.

The following features are added for VMAX:

* Extend volume
* Create volume from snapshot
* Dynamically creating masking views, storage groups,
  and initiator groups
* Striped volumes
* FAST policies

Tempest test results from CI system:
  https://bugs.launchpad.net/cinder/+bug/1337840

Change-Id: I01aaf1041d32351a8dc12c509f387e2d120074a3
Implements: blueprint emc-vmax-driver-juno-update

commit_message:
Update driver metadata definitions to Juno

vmware and libvirt support different hw_vif_model settings.
This patch updates them so that each namespace can specify
the models they support.

vmware api is updated with the vmware_disktype

Change-Id: Iec5901097c9621a052a930b99d5cbe7872d4f3ff
Closes-bug: 1370767
(cherry picked from commit ebafdbeef6420d0fcc4922f245956096ca9e50b3)

Hi, Erno Kuvaja.
Actually we have problems with parallelism only in test_migrations, which I have fixed in the previous(dependent) patch. Also, we had had problems with test_swift_store, which recently was deleted(and for which I made a fix because I have not updated master at time).'}, {'account_id': 6549, 'date': '2014-09-12 11:45:20.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2: -Code-Review

Hello Oleksii, thanks for working on this.

From the Jenkins result of nikhil's change [0] and my local testing result [1], I think there are three cases related to a race-condition issue, at least. According to now all test cases of store drivers have already been refactored and moved to glance_stroe tree/proj, so I think if this change could work well and verified by job/gate, then I'd love to see this change get merged due to adding concurrent testing to glance is a good way to go.

[0] http://logs.openstack.org/27/108427/1/check/gate-glance-python27/b67527d/testr_results.html.gz

[1] http://paste.openstack.org/show/91909/"}, {'account_id': 7491, 'date': '2014-09-12 13:02:17.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2: Code-Review+1

I've tested this change with a different concurrency and tests passed ok for me locally. Seems to be, that after test cases of store drivers were refactored, the only reason of race conditions were miration tests, which were refactored in the previous patch."}, {'account_id': 5202, 'date': '2014-09-12 20:58:50.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2:

Hi Oleksii,

That sounds great. As said, I'm personally all up for this as soon as we have seen a while the tests running parallel without breaking again. As this affects gate as well, I would not want to rush with this change, specially now under the release.

Thanks a million if you really got the issues there fixed. Lets see how stable the tests are for a while before merging this in? At least that's what I'd like to see."}, {'account_id': 12363, 'date': '2014-09-14 12:58:07.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

commit_message:
Run tests with default concurrency 0

Setting concurrency to 0 would enable Glance tests to be run using the
the total number of cores on the system rather than by a single one.

This would, by default, speed up the run time of tests for developers
who are not aware about it. Also, any jobs which run these tests for
Continuous Integration would be benefitted without having to deal with
the machine level logic.

Closes-Bug: #1368274

Change-Id: I0842b0c0be1272d479fad9ef7609cd8a29231cb5

This patch should be split into more than one changesets. I believe there are three:

1) remove the installation of several packages; the commit message makes no mention of that.

2) reorder some of the iniset_sudo calls, which is not a functional change.

3) introduce dnsmasq configuration.

With regards to 3):

a) "dhcp-option-force=26,1454" needs an echo or comment to explain what the script is doing, and why, for instance: "Using DHCP option to set interface MTU to 1454" (to be on the safe side due to GRE overhead).

b) Like Matjaz, I'd like to know what is being fixed here, so there's a chance to verify it does what it should. This is all the more important because of c).

c) This code doesn't work. You need sudo to write into that location. Clearly, this patch has never been tested by anyone, so nobody knows whether it works.'}, {'account_id': 7007, 'date': '2014-09-05 10:42:43.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Workflow-1

commit_message:
Fix use of kwargs instead of **kwargs

This but did not show well because it is used inside a handler that
ignores and logs the exception. But the domain update call fails.

Closes-Bug: #1375415

commit_message:
Add missing metadefs for shutdown behavior

The following Nova patch adds support for graceful shutdown
of a guest VM and allows setting timeout properties on images.
The properties should be updated in the Metadata Definitions catalog.

https://review.openstack.org/#/c/68942/

Change-Id: I58145d9d0114b3932b63263ea123c4662146d14b
Closes-bug: 1368036

Thanks Radomir for reviewing. The CreateUserForm and UpdateUserForm classes under openstack_dashboard/dashboards/identity/users/forms.py sets the field 'no_autocomplete = True' which causes the 2 input elements to be added - one for fake_username and one for fake_password. Since the fake_password input type is 'password', it adds a span tag to include the glyphicon-eye-open icon. The change I have added in this patch is to avoid the span element for the glyphicon-eye-open icon from being added. It doesnt per say hide the password input element. I thought of setting the no_autocomplete=False, so that the input elements for fake_username & fake_password are not added but I brought this up in IRC and it looks like its needed and I have mentioned the reason in the commit message. 

Were you thinking about removing the input elements for fake_username and fake_password coz mine only gets rid of the span element for the icon. Appreciate the feedback."}, {'account_id': 8648, 'date': '2014-09-26 05:40:59.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

The whole "fake_password" form field is supposed to be hidden with CSS rules. We have the problem with the icon appearing, because the way it was hidden with CSS rules is not very good -- the rules only hide the input element itself, instead of hiding the whole HTML generated for that field. I think that instead of piling special cases, we should just hide the whole field properly, together with the eye icon.'}, {'account_id': 10295, 'date': '2014-09-26 15:35:04.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 4.'}, {'account_id': 6825, 'date': '2014-09-26 15:39:58.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4:

commit_message:
Remove glyphicon-eye-open icon from Description

The glyphicon-eye-open icon is displayed in the Description section
of the 'Create User' and 'Update User' form under the Identify->Users
panel. This is because the no_autocomplete field has been set to
'True' for both the 'Create User' and 'Update User' forms. Enabling
this field causes an input of type="password" and name="fake_password"
to be added inorder to prevent Chrome v34+ from autofilling the form.

Change-Id: Ic628772112aae2d320d8d8342305c33d7ada6822
Closes-Bug: #1371787

commit_message:
Enhance  V2 disk_config extension Unit Test

disk_config extension extends the request/response
for server's create, update, rebuild & resize operation.
However, unit tests of the extension are not enough now.

This patch adds more tests to increase code coverage.

Change-Id: Ibdc9a931fac7501a9f8326bae16f3b41d51be9bb

commit_message:
Refactor template simple_parse

The places that use simple_parse all have to check if the returned value
is a dict, so that logic can be safely moved into simple_parse itself to
avoid duplication.

Co-Authored-By: Asif Choudhury <choudhury.asif@gmail.com>
Change-Id: I973f97fa5ce46e7492611555759d20131b98ab07

commit_message:
Enable breaking test for adopt operation

After turning off by default adopt and abandon one of the test show
traceback during unittests. This patch fix this problem, by overriding
config option for this test.

Change-Id: I8e0f8662753681079e4dd22c0726042ad47eabf0

commit_message:
Metadef Property and Object schema columns should use JSONEncodedDict

The MetadefProperty and MetadefObject ORM classes currently specify the
JSON schema columns as type Text. It is preferred to use the
JSONEncodedDict Type Decorator instead. This fix also includes necessary
code changes to remove JSON encoding/decoding that was previously done
in other layers. Fixes for unit tests involving the schema columns are
also included.

Change-Id: I2c574210f8d62c77a438afab83ff80f3e5bd2fe7
Closes-Bug: 1368479

commit_message:
Update neutron content for Juno

I updated the neutron content in the installation guide for Juno
as follows:

1) For RHEL/CentOS/Fedora, added 'which' to list of packages to
   install on controller node because of a dependency not
   managed by the python-neutronclient package.
2) Added line breaks to init script workaround to improve
   readability.
3) Fixed incorrect init script name on compute node.

Change-Id: Ide38d428e79b182e2f1d749d2580b51e7d81bd72

commit_message:
Include a 'node' key and value in ipmi metadata

The ipmi meters use resource_ids which make it challenging
to select information for all the sensors of a particular type.
This change adds metadata that identifies the physical node on
which a sensor exists.

There are still remaining issues with the naming of ipmi and
sensor-related meters that will need to be addressed separately.

Closes-Bug: 1377157
Change-Id: Ib53755112e4757aa53ab60079f3c555e21a72b63

commit_message:
render stack parameters in the correct order

Parameters in a heat template are now rendered in the order specified
in the "ParameterGroups" section. If this section is not available then
they are rendered unordered.

Change-Id: I3367b42c4c3037666b705cebf9cf67ccf0ce4fce
Closes-Bug: 1364567

[{'created': '2014-07-28 15:57:58.000000000', 'message': "Remove 'get_host_stats' virt driver API method

In Havana the following change was merged:

  commit 680cc7becc38178f47e13b3aa11c8544b1949de7
  Author: Jake Liu <jake@unitedstack.com>
  Date:   Mon Sep 2 08:56:51 2013 -0400

    Remove _report_driver_status from compute/manager.py

    After the blueprint no-compute-fanout-to-scheduler, there is no
    need for nova compute to fanout its capabilities to nova scheduler,
    so we can remove _report_driver_status as it is no use now.

This removed the last use of the 'get_host_stats' method outside
of the virt drivers themselves. There was a default implementation
of the 'get_available_nodes' method which relied on 'get_host_stats'
but that is trivially implementable directly in each driver.

There is thus no compelling reason to continue to have a public
'get_host_stats' method with such ill-defined (read: totally
undocumented) return dict.

Change-Id: I7d18fa1ab3a2f04c8b514aa4523a37a5dfb5f33c

In Havana the following change was merged:

  commit 680cc7becc38178f47e13b3aa11c8544b1949de7
  Author: Jake Liu <jake@unitedstack.com>
  Date:   Mon Sep 2 08:56:51 2013 -0400

    Remove _report_driver_status from compute/manager.py

    After the blueprint no-compute-fanout-to-scheduler, there is no
    need for nova compute to fanout its capabilities to nova scheduler,
    so we can remove _report_driver_status as it is no use now.

This removed the last use of the 'get_host_stats' method outside
of the virt drivers themselves. There was a default implementation
of the 'get_available_nodes' method which relied on 'get_host_stats'
but that is trivially implementable directly in each driver.

There is thus no compelling reason to continue to have a public
'get_host_stats' method with such ill-defined (read: totally
