commit_message:
Set non-empty external-id for bridges by default

Set external-id for bridges to their names by default.
OVS-agent monitors external bridges only if their external-id
matches their names

commit_message:
Import the camptocamp openssl module version 0.3.1.

It is a new module that will be used to manage SSL keys and
certificates. It allows:
  - The generation of SSL keys,
  - The generation of SSL certificate from private key
  - The generation of SSL certificate signing request

Change-Id: I4a6a7b78d58fd17ea133421bc326fe2d3d65b409
Implements: blueprint ssl-endpoints

The integrated api client previously did the HTTPConnection /

doesn't care about SSL certs at all. While not actually an issue for

commit_message:
move integrated api client to requests library

The integrated api client previously did the HTTPConnection /
HTTPSConnection url parsing dance. In python 2.x HTTPSConnection
doesn't care about SSL certs at all. While not actually an issue for
these tests, it does mean we keep around an example in the code that
uses HTTPSConnection, which will prevent us from creating a hacking
rule to keep those out once the other 4 actual security issues with
HTTPSConnection are removed.

Change-Id: Idd7d5a055600dda663f9c56b39883510f8688b12
Related-Bug: #1188189

commit_message:
Fixed issue with max size for Swift objects

Fixed issue with max size of object, which Glance
should store in Swift without slicing.
Default value doesn't work when user attempts to make
a snapshots with size > 300 Mb.

Change-Id: Ic3b3120605f1e1536a34bedc4ad5c0c2f4c8510b
Closes-Bug: #1373813

commit_message:
Fix unsafe SSL connection on TrustedFilter

TrustedFilter was using httplib which doesn't check for CAs.
Here the change is using Requests and verifies local CAs by default (or another
one if provided)
This effort is related to CVE 2013-2255.

SecurityImpact

Closes-Bug: #1373993

Change-Id: I0b8e6319a4cc39876b1e396ef705f0fc5def1e44
(cherry picked from commit 30871e8702737edbbfbcbbb5f21858873b37685c)

This change is to reduce VIP transition.

by default) This change enables nopreempt by default,

commit_message:
Change initial state and failback policy for VIP

This change is to reduce VIP transition.
The current defaults cause the VIP to automatically
failback to a higher priority controller or one with
a higher IP if priorities are the same ( which they are
by default) This change enables nopreempt by default,
thereby disabling automatic failback when a higher priority
controller becomes available.  It also changes the
default initial state to BACKUP (required for nopreempt).

There are also two new configurables:

   keepalived.state        - BACKUP
   keepalived.preempt      - false

Use keepalived.state=MASTER,keepalived.preempt=true for
original behaviour.

Change-Id: Ie27327286524ed93326ae49c7ca420809fb553a1

commit_message:
Wait for memory and vcpus from hypervisor stats

Building on what was added in I43d72cc0d2c1ded70af28d9861aa6e28838795bf,
this makes use of the new memory and vcpu parameters in
wait_for_hypervisor_stats to make sure that the script checks the
correct memory amount and vcpu count are available.

Change-Id: I40ac243a5c9d97264accbefe4ce96497914b6b01

commit_message:
Secure the MySQL bind-address on the seed

The MySQL bind-address on the seed should be set to
localhost for security.  Introduce a mysql.bind_address
to configure this for the seed. (mysql.local_bind sets
the bind address to the local IP for the overcloud)

Change-Id: I7faa97243c9a686badd8d11ec001480ecab4af50

commit_message:
Eliminate unnecessary search for test cases

As all unit tests lie in `ceilometer/ceilometer/tests`,
the test_command should use `ceilometer/tests` instead of `ceilometer`.

Change-Id: Idb1dade44a06c71fb5e64ca875b71633def110a5
Closes-Bug: 1368509

revisions:
[{'created': '2014-10-03 12:53:23.000000000', 'message': "provide UI control for NSX plugin 'replication_mode' setting

- NSX cluster can operate without NSX Service nodes, but this requires
  configuration of `replication_mode' setting, so lets add an
  opportunity for user to specify that his NSX cluster runs in testing
  mode (without Service nodes).

Change-Id: Ia545dd90fd7e8b3b2de7280088bd07c689b1adb7
Partial-bug: #1365043
"}]
commit_message:
provide UI control for NSX plugin 'replication_mode' setting

- NSX cluster can operate without NSX Service nodes, but this requires
  configuration of `replication_mode' setting, so lets add an
  opportunity for user to specify that his NSX cluster runs in testing
  mode (without Service nodes).

Change-Id: Ia545dd90fd7e8b3b2de7280088bd07c689b1adb7
Partial-bug: #1365043

commit_message:
Remove a duplicate ignore rule of pep8

There are two E123 declarations in tox.ini. However, we don't need the
duplication. This commit removes one.

Change-Id: I9e681b99b8b6df84ae986974ac733a380e127605

One patch is enough, just follow olso guide to create the olso files for ironic and resubmit with same change id.'}, {'account_id': 8106, 'date': '2014-09-18 07:26:31.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

Download the olso code and run below command to generate the policy.py which is synced from oslo, then commit this new file in ~/ironic-oslo/ironic/openstack/common/ with same change-id of current one:

  #git clone https://github.com/openstack/oslo-incubator
  #cd oslo-incubator/
  #mkdir ~/ironic-oslo
  #./update.sh --nodeps --base ironic --dest-dir ~/ironic-oslo --modules policy

Thanks and good luck.'}, {'account_id': 6348, 'date': '2014-09-18 07:35:20.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

Haomeng,

Thanks, I will do it.'}, {'account_id': 6773, 'date': '2014-09-18 08:41:40.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1

Yup as Haomneg just rightly pointed out, this needs to be fixed in oslo first and then sync'ed here in Ironic"}, {'account_id': 6348, 'date': '2014-09-18 09:01:40.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

Haomeng,?Lucas

It's not lucky for me to sysn policy.py in oslo and ironic, I just followed Haomeng's suggestion, but it's not a git repository, so can't commit the patch. I also found there are a lot of differences between policy.py in oslo and ironic."}, {'account_id': 6618, 'date': '2014-09-18 13:21:41.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

Hi, to be clear there are two steps to fixing this in ironic:
1. the bug is in the oslo code, so a patch needs to be submitted there. Once the fix is merged in oslo, then
2. you can submit an updated patch revision here, to get the change into ironic.'}, {'account_id': 6773, 'date': '2014-09-18 13:28:04.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

What you mean is not a git repository?

Oh so following Haoment instructions keep in mind that ~/ironic-oslo thre is your local git ironic repository, like:

 $ git clone https://github.com/openstack/oslo-incubator
 $ cd oslo-incubator/
 $ ./update.sh --nodeps --base ironic --dest-dir <YOUR LOCAL IRONIC REPO PATH> --modules policy

Now as Ruby said, this change should go to oslo-incubator and merged there before we sync it in Ironic.'}, {'account_id': 6348, 'date': '2014-09-19 00:11:19.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

Thanks a lot. The oslo patch has been made, https://review.openstack.org/#/c/122377/

Wait for that patch to be merged.'}, {'account_id': 8106, 'date': '2014-09-19 03:07:27.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

Huawei,

Thanks for the update.

And we can mark this as 'work in progress' to depends on oslo fix to be merged and get back to sync from oslo."}, {'account_id': 8106, 'date': '2014-09-19 03:13:40.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

And we are in RC release, so it is better that we have the defect raised for this patch, thank you.'}, {'account_id': 6348, 'date': '2014-09-19 03:40:41.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Workflow-1'}, {'account_id': 6348, 'date': '2014-09-23 02:35:38.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: -Workflow

Hi,

I don't have time to look into all this, but I see that there is another patch: https://review.openstack.org/#/c/97731/ "Rewrite ironic policy to use the new changes of common policy".

So is it safe to just sync the file, or does this patch depend on the work in patch 97731?'}, {'account_id': 6773, 'date': '2014-09-25 09:02:24.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3: Code-Review-1

(1 comment)

Oh, as ruby just pointed out. So seems the new policy has changes that affects the way we use it[1], so only syncing the file is not enough. Now, we already have a patch doing it[1], maybe we should follow with the author of #97731 and see if he's still working on it. 

Sorry for the whole confusion xu-haiwei :/

[1] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/97731/"}, {'account_id': 6773, 'date': '2014-09-25 09:05:38.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

Btw, I see that the author if the 97731 is not being responsive. Maybe we should take over that work, do u wanna do it?'}, {'account_id': 6348, 'date': '2014-09-25 09:39:37.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3:

Lucas Alvares Gomes

Thank you for the comment, I must confess I didn't understand what should be done to sync ironic with oslo before making this patch. I am still a little confused right now, should we sync all the modules under ironic/openstack/common directory?
That seems to be a huge job, what I wanted to do is just fixing a little miss in policy.py originally. 

Does anyone want to take over this job? I am afraid I will abandon this patch."}, {'account_id': 6773, 'date': '2014-09-25 09:50:30.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3:

hi xu-haiwei...

No we don't need to sync everything... What you did with syncing only the policy.py is correct. The problem is that this seems to be an exception case, because afair, syncing stuff over does not really break the project like that, but the new policy.py this time seems they changed some fundamental stuff in it that actually need changes to Ironic in order to accommodate the changes in the new policy.py

By taking the work over, I mean take a look at https://review.openstack.org/#/c/97731/ there's a bunch of suggestion there in the comments (Roman have pointed what seems to be the right way to do it), follow that suggestion and submit it here?

Of course, IF and ONLY IF it's something that you want/can spent time on.

And sorry for all the complications... I understand that you wanted to fix something more simple but ended up into this cross project mess :/"}, {'account_id': 6348, 'date': '2014-09-25 10:01:20.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

Hi Lucas Alvares Gomes

Ok, I will challenge this. Thanks for the explanation. :)'}, {'account_id': 6773, 'date': '2014-10-02 09:08:55.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

any news on this?'}, {'account_id': 6348, 'date': '2014-10-02 09:24:17.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

Lucas Alvares Gomes

Truly sorry, I could not find time to do this yet. If someone wants to do it, I will abandon it.'}, {'account_id': 6623, 'date': '2014-10-02 12:38:49.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: Code-Review-1

I believe there was another patch that was doing the same thing.'}, {'account_id': 6773, 'date': '2014-10-07 09:08:38.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

No problem xu-haiwei :)

Roman is working on a diff patch now https://review.openstack.org/#/c/126265/'}, {'account_id': 6773, 'date': '2014-10-07 09:08:41.000000000', 'content': 'Abandoned'}]

commit_message:
Include Metadata Defs Concepts in Dev Docs

The http://docs.openstack.org/developer/glance/
site currently doesn't include the Juno Metadata
Definitions concepts.  This patch adds
an overview of the concepts to this site.

This provides a synopis of the concepts in:
https://github.com/openstack/glance-specs/blob/master/specs/juno/metadata-schema-catalog.rst

DocImpact
Closes-Bug: 1367432
Related-Bug: 1367908
Related-Bug: 1363615
Related-Bug: 1366286
Related-Bug: 1363383
Change-Id: Iad4d388cbbf2f63fa243d04d35032de0cb0bc1b4
(cherry picked from commit 0aab5e271667990afb1a2522c7c9c61fa7211e0b)

The dhcp port is reserved by simply changing the device_id to "reserved_dhcp_port".  The relationship to the network and subnet is maintained.  Doing this keeps the allocated ip from returning to the pool and avoids allocating a new ip for a new dhcp port.  You can do a dhcp-agent-network-remove followed by a dhcp-agent-network-add or you could do several removes followed by several adds.  Doing several removes and then several adds would imply that a network is hosted by multiple dhcp agents.  This could certainly be a valid situation.  You would then end up with a pool of reserved dhcp ports after several removes.  When you do the adds, the ports can get added back in any order and you will end up with your network hosted on new dhcp agents but with ports which have maintained their ip addresses.  I don't think there is a problem.  If I'm misunderstanding the use case, let me know.'}, {'account_id': 8788, 'date': '2014-10-06 05:32:23.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1

After re-reviewing the code, and following Ed comments, I see 
you use, "for port in network.ports: ...." to look up for the reserved ports, so at worst you could just mix
up ports within a network when having HA, which is perfectly fine.

Ed, thank you for taking your time to reply and explain. And sorry for the wrong evaluation.

Ihar, the code looks ok to me.'}, {'account_id': 8645, 'date': '2014-10-06 06:53:16.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1'}, {'account_id': 9656, 'date': '2014-10-06 10:03:50.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Code-Review+2'}, {'account_id': 8213, 'date': '2014-10-07 07:57:11.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+2 Workflow+1

commit_message:
Provide way to reserve dhcp port during failovers

This change provides a way to save the dhcp port when failing
over a network from one dhcp agent to another.  When a
dhcp-agent-network-remove is issued, the dhcp port device_id is
marked as reserved which causes it to not be deleted. When a
subsequent dhcp-agent-network-add is issued, the reserved port
is used and the device_id is corrected.  This is desirable
in order to maintain the dhcp port ip address so that dns doesn't
get impacted. Unit test added.

Closes-Bug: #1288923
(cherry picked from d5c0a37999f9e3a611a322baacabebc06b13283b)
Conflicts:
	neutron/common/utils.py
	neutron/tests/unit/test_db_plugin.py

Change-Id: I531d7ffab074b01adfe186d2c3df43ca978359cd

commit_message:
Docs - update JEOS building instructions

As dib-utils has been split from diskimage-builder, the instructions are
no longer complete.

Instead advise users to install diskimage-builder from Github with pip,
solving the dependency problem.

Change-Id: I1319fa08b1f9f026d795fe24325d3d36836b1575

commit_message:
Validates controller methods exist when specified

It was possible to specify an invalid controller method in a router.
This will not cause an error until runtime. This change catches the
error much earlier in the application lifecycle. In fact with this
change errors should not be able to pass unit tests even if there is
no specific test for the behavior.

Related-bug: #1377304
Change-Id: Icc5646c143a234127a8b4ac8a74342ef3dca7e80

commit_message:
Fixes an error deleting an endpoint group project

Deleting a endpoint group project fails because the router specifies
a controller method that doesn't exist. This returns a 500 error to
the user for what should be a successful operation.

Change-Id: I3b91d8023d31555893fb944da73633a69d8e286f
Closes-bug: #1377304

commit_message:
Specify the MetadefNamespace.namespace column is not nullable

The metadef_namespaces table definition indicates the namespace
column as not accepting nulls. The related MetadefNamespace ORM class
should also indicate that the namespace column does not accept nulls
with "nullable=False" in the column definition.

Change-Id: I681747b6579a2284f23bf154889a61c639b0616d
Closes-Bug: 1367619
(cherry picked from commit 10e858d57be5e04615f390b3060c8aeadaeed954)

commit_message:
Make compute-trust.json compatible with TrustFilter

Current properties inside compute-trust.json does not match
with how TrustFilter in nova works. JSON provides True/False
boolean values but TrustFilter expects trusted/untrusted/unknown
string values. This patch repairs compute-trust.json to be
compatible with TrustFilter.

Change-Id: I26965a549daf9340621b0f18a1b845b39bac4bd8
Closes-Bug: #1369581
(cherry picked from commit 39e90f29d93f991d95092de5f93a239be1b3ca3b)

commit_message:
show correct link to compute instances in stack resource overview tab

There are two related fixes in the stacks resource overview page.
First, any resource types for which horizon does not have a link for
were getting a URL of "None" in the uuid field, and with this
change the link is suppressed if it is None. The second part involves
adding compute resources to the resource mappings, so that the uuid
field for those links to the instance detail page.

Change-Id: Ib8d51b49ac51092a3d7db6d889f4427167e5adb0
Closes-Bug: 1322162

commit_message:
Nova instance config drive Metadata Definition

A nova Juno FFE landed to support setting the
img_config_drive property on images to require images
to be booted with a config drive. The Glance Metadata
Definitions should include this property.

See Nova Blueprint:
https://blueprints.launchpad.net/nova/+spec/config-drive-image-property

Change-Id: Iffc4d4f00f3677ed1fa41233ef6cfbc5c46d8602
Closes-bug: 1367981
(cherry picked from commit 0dd620c7bd7f07935e1cea5d0bfab2a41f754d1b)

commit_message:
Add missing metadefs for Aggregate Filters

The below spec implemented in Juno added numerous properties
that can be added to Host Aggregates. The Metadata
Definitions catalog should include them.

https://github.com/openstack/nova-specs/blob/master/specs/juno/per-aggregate-filters.rst

Change-Id: Id37028b4b24ab5f6b0c4547a3c1af47bd76e61f6
Closes-bug: 1368032
(cherry picked from commit 313d4f272cbeabfdcb39de4bcb441749f56fb4d4)
